Package: BayesPLCox
Title: Bayesian Inference for Cox Models via PL and GPL Likelihoods
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Tomohiro", "Ohigashi",
      email = "ohigashi@rs.tus.ac.jp",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Bayesian inference for Cox regression models based on 
    Plackett-Luce (PL) and generalized/geometric Plackett-Luce (GPL) likelihood formulations. 
    The acronym 'PL' reflects a dual interpretation: the classical Cox partial 
    likelihood and the Plackett-Luce model for rank-ordered data, which are 
    connected through a unified probabilistic framework.
